fullDescription.text:
Reports implementations of, and calls to, the 'clone()' method and uses of the 'java.lang.Cloneable' interface. Some coding standards prohibit the use of 'clone()', and recommend using a copy constructor or a 'static' factory method instead. The inspection ignores calls to 'clone()' on arrays because it's a correct and compact way to copy an array. Example: 'class Copy implements Cloneable /*warning*/ {

    public Copy clone() /*warning*/ {
      try {
        return (Copy) super.clone(); // warning
      } catch (CloneNotSupportedException e) {
        throw new AssertionError();
      }
    }
  }' Inspection ID: UseOfClone

