    private Logger LOG = Logger.getLogger(Critical.class);
  }' After the quick-fix is applied: 'public class Significant {
    private static final Logger LOG = Logger.getLogger(Critical.class);
  }' Configure the inspection: Use the Logger class name table to specify logger class names. The inspection will report the fields that are not 'static' and 'final' and are of the type equal to one of the specified class names. Inspection ID: NonStaticFinalLogger

