Reports unnecessary unary minuses. Such expressions might be hard to understand and might contain errors. For example: 'void unaryMinus(int i) {
    int x = - -i;
  }' The following quick fixes are suggested here: Remove '-' operators before the 'i' variable: 'void unaryMinus(int i) {
    int x = i;
  }' Replace '-' operators with the prefix decrement operator: 'void unaryMinus(int i) {
    int x = --i;
  }' Another example: 'void unaryMinus(int i) {
    i += - 8;
  }' After the quick-fix is applied: 'void unaryMinus(int i) {
    i -= 8;
  }' Inspection ID: UnnecessaryUnaryMinus

