Reports chained equality comparisons. Such comparisons may be confusing: 'a == b == c' means '(a == b) == c', but possibly 'a == b && a == c' is intended. Example: 'boolean chainedEquality(boolean a, boolean b, boolean c) {
    return a == b == c;
  }' You can use parentheses to make the comparison less confusing: 'boolean chainedEquality(boolean a, boolean b, boolean c) {
    return (a == b) == c;
  }' Inspection ID: ChainedEquality

