Reports methods that are named "main", but do not have the 'public static void main(String[])' signature in Java up to 21. Starting from Java 21 Preview, inspection doesn't highlight in case of package-private, protected or instance main methods, also without parameters. Additionally main methods located in anonymous or local classes are reported. Anonymous and local classes do not have a fully qualified name and thus can't be run. Such methods may be confusing, as methods named "main" are expected to be application entry points. Example: 'class Main {
