  x /= 3;' Use the Ignore conditional operators option to ignore '&&' and '||'. Replacing conditional operators with operator assignment would change the evaluation from lazy to eager, which may change the semantics of the expression. Use the Ignore obscure operators option to ignore '^' and '%', which are less known. Inspection ID: ReplaceAssignmentWithOperatorAssignment

