fullDescription.text:
Reports redundant local variable types. These types can be inferred from the context and thus replaced with 'var'. Example: 'void test(InputStream s) {
    try (InputStream in = s) {}
  }' After the fix is applied: 'void test(InputStream s) {
    try (var in = s) {}
  }' This inspection depends on the Java feature 'Local variable type inference', which is available since Java 10. Inspection ID: RedundantExplicitVariableType

