fullDescription.text:
Reports non-'final', non-'private' fields that are accessed in a synchronized context. A non-'private' field cannot be guaranteed to always be accessed in a synchronized manner, and such "partially synchronized" access may result in unexpectedly inconsistent data structures. Example: 'class Bar {
