fullDescription.text:
Reports redundant 'else' keywords in 'if''else' statements and statement chains. The 'else' keyword is redundant when all previous branches end with a 'return', 'throw', 'break', or 'continue' statement. In this case, the statements from the 'else' branch can be placed after the 'if' statement, and the 'else' keyword can be removed. Example: 'if (name == null) {
      throw new IllegalArgumentException();
  } else {
      System.out.println(name);
  }' After the quick-fix is applied: 'if (name == null) {
      throw new IllegalArgumentException();
  }
  System.out.println(name);' Disable the Report when there are no more statements after the 'if' statement option to ignore cases where the 'if''else' statement is the last statement in a code block. Inspection ID: ConfusingElse

