Reports redundant `else` keywords in `if`---`else` statements and statement chains.


The `else` keyword is redundant when all previous branches end with a
`return`, `throw`, `break`, or `continue` statement. In this case,
the statements from the `else` branch can be placed after the `if` statement, and the
`else` keyword can be removed.

**Example:**


      if (name == null) {
          throw new IllegalArgumentException();
      } else {
          System.out.println(name);
      }

After the quick-fix is applied:


