Reports 'if' statements that throw only 'java.lang.Throwable' from a 'then' branch and do not have an 'else' branch. Such statements can be converted to more compact 'assert' statements. The inspection also reports Guava's 'Preconditions.checkNotNull()'. They can be replaced with a 'Objects.requireNonNull()' call for which a library may not be needed. Example: 'if (x == 2) throw new RuntimeException("fail");
