fullDescription.text:
Reports calls to 'java.util.Set.removeAll()' with a 'java.util.List' argument. Such a call can be slow when the size of the argument is greater than or equal to the size of the set, and the set is a subclass of 'java.util.AbstractSet'. In this case, 'List.contains()' is called for each element in the set, which will perform a linear search. Example: 'public void check(String... ss) {
    // possible O(n^2) complexity
    mySet.removeAll(List.of(ss));
  }' After the quick fix is applied: 'public void check(String... ss) {
    // O(n) complexity
    List.of(ss).forEach(mySet::remove);
  }' Inspection ID: SlowAbstractSetRemoveAll New in 2020.3

