Reports operators '==' and '!=' used to test for array equality. In most cases, testing for the equality of array contents is intended, which can be done with the 'java.util.Arrays.equals()' method. A quick-fix is suggested to replace '==' with 'java.util.Arrays.equals()'. Example: 'void foo(Object[] x, Object[] y) {
