fullDescription.text:
Reports calls to 'Condition.await()', for which no call to a corresponding 'Condition.signal()' or 'Condition.signalAll()' can be found. Calling 'Condition.await()' in a thread without corresponding 'Condition.signal()' may cause the thread to become disabled until it is interrupted or "spurious wakeup" occurs. Only calls that target fields of the current class are reported by this inspection. Example: 'class Queue {
