  static List<String> readFileAndTrim(String path) throws IOException {
    Path p = Path.of(path);
    List<String> lines = Files.readAllLines(p);
    return lines.stream().map(String::trim).toList();
  }' Here, the second method is quite similar to the first one, and the first one can be reused in its implementation. After the quick-fix is applied, the result will look like this: 'static List<String> readFileAndTrim(Path path) throws IOException {
    List<String> lines = Files.readAllLines(path);
    return lines.stream().map(String::trim).toList();
  }

  static List<String> readFileAndTrim(String path) throws IOException {
