Reports issues with 'AtomicLongFieldUpdater', 'AtomicIntegerFieldUpdater', or 'AtomicReferenceFieldUpdater' fields (the 'java.util.concurrent.atomic' package). The reported issues are identical to the runtime problems that can happen with atomic field updaters: specified field not found, specified field not accessible, specified field has a wrong type, and so on. Examples: 'class A {
