This inspection depends on the Java feature 'Lambda expressions', which is available since Java 8.

Inspection ID: LambdaCanBeReplacedWithAnonymous

fullDescription.text:
Reports text blocks that can be replaced with regular string literals. This may help to downgrade for backward compatibility with earlier Java versions. Example: 'Object obj = engine.eval("""
                           function hello() {
                             print('"Hello, world"');
                           }

                           hello();
                           """);' After the quick fix is applied: 'Object obj = engine.eval("function hello() {\n" +
                           "  print('\"Hello, world\"');\n" +
                           "}\n" +
                           "\n" +
                           "hello();\n");' This inspection depends on the Java feature 'Text block literals', which is available since Java 15. Inspection ID: TextBlockBackwardMigration New in 2019.3

