fullDescription.text:
Reports arithmetic expressions with the excessive number of terms. Such expressions might be hard to understand and might contain errors. Parameters, field references, and other primary expressions are counted as a term. Example: 'int calc(int a, int b) {
        return a + a + a + b + b + b + b; // The line contains 7 terms and will be reported.
    }' Use the field below to specify a number of terms allowed in arithmetic expressions. Inspection ID: OverlyComplexArithmeticExpression

