fullDescription.text:
Reports 'switch' statements or expressions that contain the same code in different branches and suggests merging the duplicate branches. Example: 'switch (n) {
    case 1:
      System.out.println(n);
      break;
    case 2:
      System.out.println(n);
      break;
    default:
      System.out.println("default");
  }' After the quick-fix is applied: 'switch (n) {
    case 1:
    case 2:
      System.out.println(n);
      break;
    default:
      System.out.println("default");
  }' Inspection ID: DuplicateBranchesInSwitch New in 2019.1

