fullDescription.text:
Reports cases where the minimum or the maximum of two numbers can be calculated using a 'Math.max()' or 'Math.min()' call, instead of doing it manually. Example: 'public int min(int a, int b) {
    return b < a ? b : a;
  }' After the quick-fix is applied: 'public int min(int a, int b) {
    return Math.min(a, b);
  }' Use the Disable for float and double option to disable this inspection for 'double' and 'float' types. This is useful because the quick-fix may slightly change the semantics for 'float'/ 'double' types when handling 'NaN'. Nevertheless, in most cases this will actually fix a subtle bug where 'NaN' is not taken into account. Inspection ID: ManualMinMaxCalculation New in 2019.2

