ding functions do have arguments and a non-void return type. Therefore, they also will not be executed by the JUnit test runner. This inspection will also report about this problem. Malformed '@Before' method example: '@Before private int foo(int arg) { }' After the quick-fix is applied: '@Before public void foo() { }' Missing method source example (Kotlin): 'class Example {
